        Official Singles Chart on 27/8/2021

        27 August 2021 - 2 September 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Weekly Chart Review:

        I’m aware you all think I’m a troll now, but I assure you my comments here will remain the same tone and level of negativity and pessimism as they always have been. Have a nice week everyone, including Frank ig.

        🔴 Bad:

        •New Entry in the form of ‘Wid It’, not a good song at all. It’s quite a shame how much drill has increased in popularity this year, in my opinion. The line about Essex lips made me chuckle though.

        • ’Our Song’ by Anne-Marie and Niall Horan has gone onto ACR, which is such a shame, however they haven’t done themselves much of a favour by removing the original and the Luca Shreiner remix from Amazon Prime.

        • ‘Essence’ is still climbing, which is an awful song. I’m yet to hear JBs version, but I can’t imagine it being much better than the version played on R1.

        • ‘Fly Away’ and ‘Kiss My (Uh Oh)’ continue to avoid the top 10, despite horrors such as ‘Wasted’ and ‘Talk About’ having places.

        • ‘MONTERO (Call Me By Your Name)’ has left the top 40 for the first time. Dang 😢

        🟡 Mixed:

        • ‘GUESS IM IN LOVE’ debuts at number 22, and it’s a good song, but Clinton Kane is a one trick pony, and it’s not much different to CHICKEN TENDIES, or any of his other stuff.

        • ‘Bad Habits’ has tied ‘drivers license’ for longest number one of the year, and is on track to overtake. This song has massively worn off on me and as happy as I am for Ed, I’m p*ssed at him for stealing ‘good 4 u’s final weeks, and for keeping ‘STAY’ away from the top spot. I feel like it could even go on to hold it for longer than ‘Shape Of You’ but if it takes the top spot on the year end charts, I’ll be well mad.

        • ‘Drive’ and ‘Just For Me’ both climb. Meh.

        🟢 Positive:

        • ‘Visiting Hours’ scores highest new entry. It’s more traditional Ed, but it’s such a beautiful song and I’m glad it scores him another top 5.

        • ‘Need To Know’ and ‘Woman’ reach new peaks and ‘Kiss Me More’ replaces ‘Is Sh*t’. Doja is doing so well for herself and I’m chuffed.

        • The Dave tracks are all dropping. Need I say more?
